From 262aad9340f2e9353d835c35578e5aec051f7fb2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 11:43:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(orchestrator): MCP-grounded remediation loop with
 operator escalation

When a chat-driven plan fails mid-execution, re-prompt the LLM with a
fresh, leaf-targeted MCP snapshot and the per-attempt failure log so it
can correct against reality instead of re-firing the same command. If
retries exhaust or the LLM emits `needs_help:`, deliver the question to
the operator as a chat reply (success=True, plan_executed=False) instead
of silently failing the turn.

- leaf_sender: surface phase-2 ERROR (was swallowing SetFormation aborts)
  and expose last_failure() with leaf_type/phase/error.
- plan_executor: record executor.failed_leaf on first False return.
- mcp_readonly_provider: get_targeted_context(failure) biases planned
  calls by failed leaf type (formation -> /formations/status, mapf ->
  get_action_status /swarm/set_goals); summarize_for_remediation drops
  topology listings.
- user_prompt: build_remediation_prompt reuses build_user_prompt and
  appends rubric + failed plan + attempt log.
- no_execute: is_help_request recognises needs_help: / clarify: prefixes.
- chat_server: loop with stale-MCP fallback; _finalize_help banner.
- user_chat_node: CLI mirror (no MCP refresh).
- orchestrator.yaml: remediation_enabled, max_remediation_attempts=2.
- prompts: document escalation prefixes + examples.
- tests: 15 new unit tests; full suite passes locally.

